
    THE South African Students Congress (SASCO) in the Mopani
region shut down the Mopani TVET College in Phalaborwa in Limpopo on
Wednesday.SASCO is not happy about the decrease in
student enrolment and also accused the campus of charging them fees while
president Jacob Zuma announced that government would subsidize free high
education for the poor and working class.SASCO Secretary in Mopani region Rakgotsoka Afrika
said they are also not happy about the denial of enrolment for students who owe
